==Latin==
In Latin, the letter J is a modern typographical convention for the [[consonant]] form of [[I]].  The letter I in ancient times represented either a [[vowel]] or a consonant, see [[I#Latin|I]] for more information.

===Pronunciation===
* Classical: IPA: /j/

